body:
```verilog
module test;
`define MAX(_a, _b) ((_a) > (_b) ? (_a) : (_b))
localparam integer X = `MAX($clog2(1 << 17) - 18, 0);
initial $display("%d", X);
endmodule
```
This will lead to X = -1 quite unexpectedly.

This is because clog2 returns an unsigned (=17) then when subtracting 18, this leads to an underflow which throws the comparison used in the MAX.

Reading the Verilog 2005 spec, Section 17.11.1 seems to indicate the return type of clog2 should be 'integer' which is signed. (even though the actual result can never be negative obviously).

